# SEO & Deployment

## Canonical Host

- Primary: `https://blog.sandeepallala.com` (no www, no trailing slash)
- `netlify.toml` has a 301 redirect from `www.blog.sandeepallala.com` → `blog.sandeepallala.com`
- `next.config.ts` sets `trailingSlash: false`

## Metadata

Every page should include:
- `alternates.canonical` with full URL
- `openGraph` (title, description, url, type, siteName)
- `twitter` card metadata

Example from `app/blog/page.tsx`:
```tsx
export const metadata = {
  alternates: { canonical: `${SITE_URL}/blog` },
  openGraph: { url: `${SITE_URL}/blog`, type: 'website', siteName: 'Code Chronicles' },
  twitter: { card: 'summary_large_image' },
};
```

## Deployment

- **Platform**: Netlify with `@netlify/plugin-nextjs`
- **Build**: `npm run build` (Node 20)
- **Auto-deploy**: Push to `main` triggers deploy
- `app/sitemap.ts` and `app/robots.ts` generate sitemap and robots.txt dynamically

## Known SEO Issue

Google Search Console showed "Page with redirect" for some pages. Root causes addressed:
- Trailing slash redirects (fixed with `trailingSlash: false`)
- www vs non-www (fixed with Netlify 301 redirect)
- Missing canonical tags on index pages (fixed with explicit metadata)
